Here's an example of how you could build a calculator using HTML, JavaScript and a bit of CSS for styling:

#### HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title> Calculator </title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
<div id="calculator">

  <div id="display">0</div>
  <button id="ac">AC</button>
  <button id="ce">CE</button>

  <div class="num" id="seven">7</div>
  <div class="num" id="eight">8</div>
  <div class="num" id="nine">9</div>
  <div class="operator" id="divide">/</div>

  <div class="num" id="four">4</div>
  <div class="num" id="five">5</div>
  <div class="num" id="six">6</div>
  <div class="operator" id="multiply">x</div>

  <div class="num" id="one">1</div>
  <div class="num" id="two">2</div>
  <div class="num" id="three">3</div>
  <div class="operator" id="subtract">-</div>

  <div class="num" id="zero">0</div>
  <div class="num" id="decimal">.</div>
  <div class="operator" id="add">+</div>

  <div class="equal" id="equal">=</div>
</div> <!-- end of calculator div -->

<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

